        <prompt>What was the main effect of the Supreme Court's Civil Rights Cases?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It severely limited federal civil rights enforcement</option>
            <option letter="b">It expanded civil rights</option>
            <option letter="c">It protected equality</option>
            <option letter="d">It opposed segregation</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The 1883 Civil Rights Cases severely limited federal power to protect civil rights by ruling that the 14th Amendment only restricted state actions.</explanation>
